The Zaria Zonal Command of Kaduna state Vigilante Service (KadVS) on Saturday arrested four bridegrooms for violating the ban on large gatherings imposed by the state government. Bala Galadima, Zaria Zonal Commandant of KadVS, said the arrests were made at Lowcost, Mangwaron Babayo, Magajiya and Bakin Kasuwa settlements. The Zonal Commandant said that the service had earlier reacted to intelligence information to facilitate the arrests of a bride, her groom and other guests at a marriage ceremony in the city on Wednesday. Kano bans carrying of passengers in car boots Kano bans carrying of passengers in car boots Security agents raid another rehab centre, arrest four teachers in Kaduna